content.description: Traverse the obvious set of ledges until you reach the big hole/sidepull. Throw a heel next to your hands and throw up to the next hueco and then aim for the pocket with your right hand. From here it is easy climbing to the top, but it is a little high, so keep climbing and you got it from there.
content.protection: Have pads in case you drop from the top. Big fall.
content.location: The start is on the right of where the ledges begin.

content.description: Start at holds about 8 feet high and get your heel up to the little cup to the right. throw to a good ledge above you then move left. Across the crack there is a pocket crimp to get to with your left hand. Then hit the slot ledge with your right. Slap up hard to the sloper top and prepare to bump that right hand to a God like ledge. Hold on and top her out.
content.location: Left of Mr. Bob. You will notice the hole towards the top of the crack.

content.description: Start right hand pocket, left hand on the incut part of the crack to the left. Establish yourself on the two crimps then throw for the deep sloper. Match and work the top part of the slab. Be careful not to mantel on choss to the right. Stay right of the crack system and go straight up the slab.
content.location: Right of the boob and left of The God slap.
